The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Wednesday, April 21, 2004 				 Indo Rama mulls retail foray 
 RAJA GHOSHAL 																								New Delhi, April 20: Polyester major Indo Rama Synthetics (India) Limited is likely to make a foray into the booming retailing sector by the end of the year. 																								Sources close to the company said the retail business, to be launched in the sector of food and agro-business, will commence its operation in Delhi and will subsequently be rolled out nationally. 																								Speaking to The Telegraph, .P. Lohia, managing director, said, We are forming a separate company for the retailing business, but the name has not been finalised. He confirmed that the business would be in the sector of food and grocery retailing. 																								Indo Rama recorded a 37.57 per cent increase in its annual net profit at Rs 171.71 crore from Rs 124.82 crore last year. However, sales remained flat at Rs 2,196.41 crore as against Rs 2,173.05 crore last year. The company announced a dividend of 20 per cent for the fiscal ended March 31 this year.																								The company attributed this to an enhanced other income of 102.42 crore, as against that of only Rs 32,54 crore last year. 
